article.headline: Ark.-Pine Bluff 73, Alabama A&amp,M 60
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. -- Terrance Calvin scored 18 points and Arkansas-Pine Bluff defeated Alabama A&M 73-60 on Monday night to end a two-game skid. The Golden Lions (8-14, 7-4 Southwestern Athletic Conference) snapped the Bulldogs' two-game winning streak while beating them for the second time this season. Arkansas-Pine Bluff led 39-21 at intermission, thanks in part to Alabama A&M's 26.7-percent first-half field goal shooting (8 of 30). The Golden Lions held a 41-21 advantage with 19:46 left, but were only 8-for-16 from the field in the second half. That allowed the Bulldogs (7-12, 5-6) to trim the deficit to eight points on three occasions, the last at 61-53 with 3:46 left. Arkansas-Pine Bluff responded with five straight points. Tyree Glass added 13 points for the Golden Lions and Eric Brooks had 12. Jonathan Inman scored 19 points to pace Alabama A&M.
